Interesting philosophical implication

Your earlier thought about oscillating between pattern and substrate actually fits modern complexity science.

Life may emerge from a tension between:

order (patterns)
and
exploration (randomness / noise)

Too much order → rigidity
Too much randomness → chaos

Evolution sits in the middle region.

